sql:
SELECT project_name
FROM projects
WHERE status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- A "failed test" refers to a test with a success status of 0 (false); 
- "Production environment" is an environment where the final version of the system is deployed and used by end-users; 
- "Latest failed test" is the most recent test that failed for each project.

sql:
SELECT MAX(metric_value)
FROM project_metrics
WHERE metric_type = 'model_performance';

SELECT metric_value
FROM project_metrics
WHERE metric_type = 'model_performance';

SELECT project_id, AVG(metric_value) AS average_metric
FROM project_metrics
GROUP BY project_id;
